node.text:
In March, @AirbnbExperiences hosts all over the world had to stop doing what they love—sharing their interests and passions with others. 
Over the past few weeks, they’ve offered ideas for how to continue hosting even while we’re apart. 
They’ve adapted recipes based on what’s in their pantries, turned living rooms into yoga studios, and choreographed dances for families at home.

Today we’re excited to announce that Airbnb Experiences are now online. You can take a flamenco class with Lidón in Madrid, participate in a tarot card reading with Mak in Austin, or visit a colony of penguins in Cape Town—all from home.

True to Airbnb Experiences in real life, Online Experiences are hosted by remarkable people and set in small groups. Alongside making a new dish, maybe you’ll make a new friend, too.

Thank you to our incredible hosts around the world. We’ll see you online soon —> link in bio.

node.title: Meet Homage Hospitality, the hosts who built the hotel they always wanted.

node.accessibility_caption:
Inside a brick loft with high ceilings where two round light fixtures hang. The room has a table for four, a couch, and a bike hanging on the wall.
The furthest wall is of glass looking outside.

node.text:
The only thing this former factory makes now is happiness. Superhost Gonzalo’s spacious loft puts you in the heart of Colegiales, a quiet neighborhood near the buzz of Palermo Hollywood. To dive into the city’s past and present, walk to the vast flea market nearby.

Link in bio for room to breathe in the city.

Photo: @mybelohost

node.accessibility_caption: Wooden steps lead to a treehouse platform with a round sauna amongst the forest trees.

node.text:
Come home to a tree-sauna after a day on the Golden Skybridge and nearby trails. Sauna access is included with Superhost Jason’s tiny cabin, as is his knowledge of the area, which comes in handy when six different national parks are a short drive away. 

Link in bio for home sweat home.

Photo: @goldentinyhomes

node.accessibility_caption:
French villa with red brick roof, white walls, and a stone hut to the right. A man sits with his feet inside a blue rectangle pool built into a wooden
deck. The deck is surrounded by green grass.

node.text:
Véronique’s renovated farmhouse is perfectly situated for dipping your toes in the Landes countryside—or diving right in. Recent guests have appreciated daily visits from deer, but if you don’t mind missing one, take a day trip to the beaches of the Côte d’Argent. 

Link in bio for villa on historic farm. 

Photo: @philipp_franke26

node.accessibility_caption: An A-Frame cabin with dark green roof and triangle windows look over to uninterrupted views of the southern side of the Zion Mountains in Utah. A bright blue sky with white clouds, the red Zion Mountains, and green trees.

node.text:
The first thing to do after waking up in Superhost Mindy’s tiny A-frame is to open up one side to let in the whole view. Zion National Park is a short drive away, but slot canyon trails even closer will take your breath away just as quickly, by exertion or beauty or both. 

Link in bio for hiking and hot tub. 

Photo: @ethanabitz

node.accessibility_caption: Blue sky above a modern home with a flat roof in the California desert. A man stands in the frame looking at the house.

node.text:
Trent’s hillside roost gives you an elevated view of the desert. For an unforgettable one, scramble up the mountain of boulders right behind the house, ideally in time for sunrise. And don’t wait until your last day to read the guest book, which is packed with local tips.

Link in bio for constellations and coyotes.

Photo: @rockyroostcabin

node.text:
This week, we shared that Airbnb.org will be offering free, temporary housing to 20,000 Afghan refugees worldwide. These stays are being paid for through contributions to Airbnb.org from Airbnb and Brian Chesky, as well as donors to the Airbnb.org Refugee Fund.

Since the announcement, we have received enormous interest from people within the Airbnb community and beyond looking for ways to support this work with partner organizations to house Afghan refugees. 

The response has been overwhelming and today we’re sharing more details on how people can help us expand on efforts to do more to meet this unprecedented need for temporary, emergency stays for refugees arriving from Afghanistan.

Airbnb and Airbnb.org are committed to covering the cost of 20,000 stays, but with your help, we can do even more. To learn about how to support efforts to house Afghan refugees, visit the link in our bio.

node.accessibility_caption: Bright turquoise pool surrounded by smooth white walls with two wooden lounge chairs. There are palm trees in the background and a wall of green hedge on the right. A large hurrican vase with a candle sits on the edge of the left side of the pool.

node.text:
Superhost Kristin made her little house hard to leave, but don’t let that keep you from getting to know this multifaceted port town. Start at its ruined hilltop castle and make sure to arrange at least one meal at L’Escoleta, where the local seafood is almost too beautiful to eat. 

Link in bio for Costa Blanca gem.

Photo: @housita_denia

node.accessibility_caption: A Scandinavian style living room inside a barn. Two arm chairs face a wall of windows overlooking the Catskills with a blue sky and green trees. Two white sofas face each other with a wood coffee table in the center. Behind the couches are wooden support beams with an upstairs loft area.

node.text:
The wall of windows looking out on the Catskills might be the showstopper, but every element of Superhost Gun’s converted barn seems designed to inspire. Wander 14 acres of fields and walking paths, or just hang out by the pond with the birds and bullfrogs. 

Link in bio for haven by the Hudson.

Photos: @christinalau_

node.accessibility_caption: A Scandinavian style living room inside a barn. Two arm chairs face a wall of windows overlooking the Catskills with a blue sky and green trees. Two white sofas face each other with a wood coffee table in the center. Behind the couches are wooden support beams with an upstairs loft area.

A wood coffee table topped with books, a round bowl, a vase filled with white hydrangeas, and two candles on pillars. With a white couch behind it that has multiple patterned pillows. The right wall is filled with windows. Behind the couch is wooden support beams to an upstairs loft.
An off-white bookshelf with 3 shelves. The first has a small wooden red horse, the second a vase with dried pink hydrangeas, and the last has a black hat box. Against an off-white textured wall.
A kitchen with a marble island and two antique stools on one side and two wooden chairs on the other. Behind, a white wooden staircase and kitchen counter with appliances.
The living room with the sun setting in focus out the windows overlooking the Catskills. The sunbeam radiates through the bottom window. There is a wooden coffee table and white couch.
A straw bungalow in a Philippines jungle surrounded by palm trees. A green long surf board lays against the left side.

node.text:
Tucked away near the less-visited northern tip of the island, Pierre’s elegantly simple hut has nothing you don’t need. (Assuming your needs include an open-sky shower and extreme proximity to a pristine beach for surfing, exploring rock pools, or waiting for the sunset.)

Link in bio for tropical tranquility.

Photo: @noabangka

Montefalco, Italy sits in the center framed by Italian cypress trees against a

node.text:
Step-free accessibility makes it easy to enjoy this farmhouse surrounded by vineyards and olive groves. As for the view, one recent guest says, “even our two pre-teen children stopped teasing each other and just stared.” Warning: Unless you’re here for quite a while, you won’t have time to visit every charming medieval village nearby. Try to choose two or three. 

Link in bio for Superhost Lorenzo’s accessible retreat.

node.text:
A two-story gazebo is just one of this mountaintop cabin’s many places to bask in the beauty of the Smokies. Lee and Christie, your Superhosts, will also point you toward their favorite nearby adventures, from tubing on the Little River to a Dollywood ending.
 
Link in bio for Wears Valley getaway.

Link in bio for the leafy life.
